'''库罗卡河'''（{{lang-pt|'''Rio Curoca'''}}）是[[安哥拉|安哥拉]]南部[[纳米贝省|纳米贝省]]的一条间歇河，旱季时会形成残留潟湖。其是流经[[伊奥纳国家公园|伊奥纳国家公园]]的两条河流之一。<ref>[http://www.cbd.int/doc/world/ao/ao-nr-04-en.pdf FRAMEWORK REPORT ON ANGOLA’S BIODIVERSITY] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbd.int/doc/world/ao/ao-nr-04-en.pdf |date=20190817104824 }}, Soki Kuedikuenda, Miguel N. G. Xavier, Ministry of Environment, Angola, 2009</ref><ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.africanbudgetsafaris.com/locations/namib-desert/| title= Namib Desert| accessdate= 2020-07-30| archive-date= 2018-07-08| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180708162442/https://www.africanbudgetsafaris.com/locations/namib-desert/| dead-url= no}} Saturday, 21 July 2018</ref>库罗卡河组成伊奥那国家公园北部边界的一部分，也经过纳米布地方自然公园 (''Parque Natural Regional do Namibe'')的Lagoa dos Arcos绿洲。河流在[[通布阿|通布阿]]以北流入大西洋。潟湖滋养了竹子、荆棘等植物和跳羚、大羚羊等动物在此生长。Lagoa dos Arcos绿洲则是一个旅游景点。<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=8WeNJD2RW3YC&pg=PA206&lpg=PA206&dq=curoca+municipality+river&source=bl&ots=7oamKigPoR&sig=66cO9ZfKNleSmxKoy4DQiojcUg4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=UMfGUuDmK4P1oASitYHoCw&ved=0CE8Q6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=curoca%20municipality%20river&f=false Sustainable Tourism V] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8WeNJD2RW3YC&pg=PA206&lpg=PA206&dq=curoca+municipality+river&source=bl&ots=7oamKigPoR&sig=66cO9ZfKNleSmxKoy4DQiojcUg4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=UMfGUuDmK4P1oASitYHoCw&ved=0CE8Q6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=curoca%20municipality%20river&f=false |date=20141019211054 }}, F. D. Pineda, C. A. Brebbia,WIT Press, 2012</ref>季节性洪水使该地能维持少量的农牧业。

居住在库罗卡河附近的[[萨恩人|萨恩人]]原操一种叫{{link-en|Kwadi language}}的语言，但已经灭绝，现在该族人改说班图语族语言。<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=p-7ON7Rvx_AC&pg=PT942&lpg=PT942&dq=curoca+ethnic&source=bl&ots=RGCE_n5eM8&sig=AovmUzNC5Q2IvDScl3XgdkwykTo&hl=en&sa=X&ei=y77GUoXRCdbioAS8l4DQBw&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=curoca%20ethnic&f=false Encyclopedia of the World's Endangered Languages] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=p-7ON7Rvx_AC&pg=PT942&lpg=PT942&dq=curoca+ethnic&source=bl&ots=RGCE_n5eM8&sig=AovmUzNC5Q2IvDScl3XgdkwykTo&hl=en&sa=X&ei=y77GUoXRCdbioAS8l4DQBw&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=curoca%20ethnic&f=false |date=20141027172442 }}, Christopher Moseley, Routledge, Dec 6, 2012,</ref>

